Package gameobjects

This package contains game object classes for a brick-breaking style game. Key classes include: - Ball: Handles the behaviors of the game's ball, including collisions. - Brick: Represents bricks in the game with various collision strategies. - Paddle: Manages the player-controlled paddle's logic and movement. - Heart: A power-up object that can affect player's lives. - NumericLifeCounter and GraphicLifeCounter: Display and manage the player's life count. - MockBall and ExtraPaddle: Specialized classes for testing or extended gameplay features. These classes extend GameObject and are used to create the interactive elements of the game, each with its own unique properties and behaviors.
Version:
Java 11
Author:
Noam Shabat
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ball
    Represents a ball in the game, responsible for handling ball-specific behaviors such as collisions.
    Brick
    Represents a brick in the game, which can have multiple collision strategies and behaviors.
    ExtraPaddle
    Represents an additional paddle with potentially different behaviors or properties from the main paddle.
    GraphicLifeCounter
    Manages a graphical representation of the player's lives in the game.
    Heart
    Represents a heart object in the game, typically used for increasing player lives or similar power-ups.
    MockBall
    A variant of the Ball class with additional behaviors.
    NumericLifeCounter
    Manages the numeric representation of the player's lives in the game.
    Paddle
    Represents the paddle in the game, handling its logic and movements.
